author: Hadriana Lowenkron, Gabrielle Coppola
description: The US is set to announce that Nexperia BV, a Dutch semiconductor company with facilities in China, will resume shipping chips, according to a person familiar with the matter, following a trade pact agreed to by Donald Trump and Xi Jinping at their summit this week.
title: US to Announce Nexperia Chip Shipments From China to Resume

author: Craig Stirling
description: Prime Minister Giorgia Meloni’s push to rehabilitate Italy as a borrower just advanced another step as Scope Ratings raised its outlook on the country.
title: Italy’s Outlook Lifted as Scope Lauds Fiscal Repair Under Meloni

author: Eric Martin, Stephan Kueffner
description: Ecuador’s President Daniel Noboa is seeking to meet US President Donald Donald Trump within days of a Nov. 16 vote on whether to change the nation’s constitution, the 37-year-old heir to a banana empire said.
title: Ecuador’s Noboa Seeks Trump Summit Near Key Referendum

author: Daniele Lepido, Alberto Brambilla
description: Italian prosecutors ordered the seizure of around €1.3 billion ($1.5 billion) in shares from the holding company that controls the drinks maker Davide Campari-Milano NV, as part of an alleged tax-fraud probe, according to a statement late Friday.
title: Italy Seizes €1.3 Billion Campari Shares in Tax-Fraud Probe

author: Hadriana Lowenkron
description: Impacts of the government shutdown are starting to expand.
title: Trump Returns to a Capital at a Standstill and No Deal in Sight

author: Andreina Itriago, Eric Martin
description: President Donald Trump is using dramatic military deployments and strikes on suspected drug-trafficking vessels to pressure Venezuela and Colombia under the banner of a regional anti-narcotics campaign.
title: Why Trump Is Flexing US Power In Waters Off Venezuela, Colombia

author: William Horobin
description: French Prime Minister Sebastien Lecornu called for behind-closed-door talks with lawmakers as he strains to pass a budget, after an acrimonious parliamentary debate failed to find a compromise on a wealth tax.
title: France’s Lecornu Calls Lawmaker Talks as Budget Progress Falters

author: Jason Leopold
description: Democratic lawmakers on the House’s top oversight committee called upon the panel’s Republican chair to authorize a series of subpoenas to nearly two-dozen major banks about any accounts they held for disgraced financier Jeffrey Epstein.
title: House Democrats Urge Bank Subpoenas Over New Epstein Disclosures

author: Candido Mendes
description: Angola plans to cut spending by a modest 1.7% next year to 33.24 trillion kwanza ($31.2 billion), according to budget document posted on Finance Ministry website.
title: Angola to Cut 2026 Budget by 1.7% to 33.2 Trillion Kwanza

author: Martin Z Braun
description: New York state’s projected budget deficit narrowed by more than $3 billion, as the state expects a record-breaking stock market and improved outlook for Wall Street bonuses.
title: Wall Street Boom to Reduce New York Budget Deficit by $3 Billion

author: Zoe Tillman, Brian Dowling
description: Two federal judges ruled the Trump administration’s decision to suspend food-aid benefits for tens of millions of Americans during the government shutdown is likely unlawful and that US officials must use contingency funding to at least partially keep the program operational.
title: Courts Order Trump to Keep Paying Food Stamps Amid Shutdown

author: Jennifer A Dlouhy
description: High-level US representatives are staying away from the UN climate negotiations in Brazil, even as President Donald Trump seeks to influence energy policy globally.
title: US Officials to Skip UN Climate Talks Trump Derided as ‘Scam’

author: Denis Chabrol
description: Guyanese politician Azruddin Mohamed and his wealthy father, Nazar, were taken into custody on a US extradition request three days before the younger Mohamed was expected to be sworn in as opposition leader in the South American nation’s parliament.
title: Guyanese Opposition Leader Arrested on US Extradition Request

author: Michael Hirtzer, Skylar Woodhouse
description: President Donald Trump wants farmers to go out and buy bigger tractors after the US reached a long-awaited trade deal with China to restart soybean exports. But farm machinery producers might have to wait a little longer for a turnaround in sales.
title: Trump Tells Farmers to Buy Tractors, But There’s No Rush Yet

author: Matthew Malinowski
description: Chile libertarian presidential candidate Johannes Kaiser has pulled even with right-wing rival José Antonio Kast for second place in one of the final polls before the Nov. 16 vote, a surge in support that threatens to upend the race to lead one of Latin America’s richest nations.
title: Chile Outsider Johannes Kaiser Surges and Ties Kast in Presidential Poll

author: Allyson Versprille
description: US air travel is beginning to show real signs of strain as the government shutdown drags on, with traffic controller shortages snarling thousands of flights running into the weekend.
title: US Air Travel Delays Piling Up as Shutdown Strains Staffing

author: Steven T. Dennis
description: The peculiar US political phenomenon known as the filibuster is once again in focus. The filibuster is the prerogative enjoyed by the minority party in the Senate to demand never-ending debate to thwart legislation, which must be approved by both that body and the House of Representatives.
title: Trump Is Calling for the ‘Nuclear Option’ to Kill the Filibuster. What’s that Mean?

author: William Horobin
description: French lawmakers rejected wealth tax proposals in a budget debate that risks toppling Prime Minister Sebastien Lecornu.
title: French National Assembly Rejects Wealth Tax Proposals for Budget

author: Hadriana Lowenkron
description: US President Donald Trump said he would cut all fentanyl-related tariffs on Chinese goods if Beijing cracks down on exports of the drug and precursor chemicals used to make it.
title: Trump Says US Would Lift China Fentanyl Tariff If Xi Cracks Down

author: Hadriana Lowenkron
description: President Donald Trump denied that he is considering strikes on Venezuela, contradicting a media report that he’d given approval for such a move as well as his own past statements that he was preparing land attacks after a series of boat strikes.
title: Trump Denies Reports That He’s Planning Strikes on Venezuela

author: Danielle Bochove
description: Canada plans to send a massive Russian cargo plane to Ukraine if it wins legal proceedings to formally seize the aircraft.
title: Seized Russian Plane Bound for Ukraine if Canada Wins Court Case

author: Ellen Milligan, Kate Sullivan
description: The UK government is leaning toward a career diplomat as its next ambassador to the US, as Keir Starmer seeks to move on from Peter Mandelson’s resignation.
title: UK Seeks to Turn Page on Mandelson Scandal With US Envoy Pick

author: Isabelle Lee
description: Wall Street is riding this era of American state capitalism — tracking it, packaging it and offering it back to investors through a new ETF.
title: Want to Mimic What Stocks the US Buys? There May Be an ETF Soon

author: Silvia Martinez, Patrick Gillespie
description: Former Argentine President Cristina Fernandez de Kirchner blamed one of her disciples, Buenos Aires Governor Axel Kicillof, for a bruising loss to Javier Milei in midterm elections last Sunday, the clearest sign yet that the Peronist movement is plagued again by infighting.
title: Argentina’s Kirchner Blames Kicillof for Election Loss to Milei

author: Faith DiBiagio, Martin Z Braun
description: Money managers are fielding queries from worried investors about what New York City mayoral frontrunner Zohran Mamdani means for the city’s finances.
title: NYC Bond Investors Urged to Stay Calm Over Mamdani Fears

author: Danielle Bochove, Laura Dhillon Kane, Melissa Shin
description: US President Donald Trump said he received an apology from Canadian Prime Minister Mark Carney over a television ad that opposed tariffs, but suggested that trade talks between the two countries won’t restart.
title: Trump Says Canada Trade Talks Won’t Resume, Contradicting Wright

author: Donato Paolo Mancini
description: Italian Deputy Prime Minister Antonio Tajani called on the European Central Bank to lower borrowing costs and resume quantitative easing to help prevent gains in the euro from hurting his country’s exporters.
title: Italy’s Deputy Prime Minister Urges ECB to Cut Rates, Restart QE

author: Helen Nyambura
description: Unrest in Tanzania following this week’s election that barred the incumbent president’s main rivals left about 100 people dead, Amnesty International said. The country’s biggest opposition party said hundreds more may have been killed.
title: Tanzanian Election Violence Leaves 100 People Dead, Group Says

author: Jordan Fabian
description: The US has selected targets in Venezuela, including military facilities, that it may strike as part of its counter-narcotics campaign, according to reports in the Wall Street Journal and the Miami Herald.
title: Trump Officials Identify Venezuela Strike Targets, Reports Say

author: Patrick Van Oosterom
description: The center-left Democrats 66 party won the Dutch election, on track to nearly triple its presence in parliament and dealing a major blow to the anti-migrant, populist party of Geert Wilders.
title: Center-Left Dutch Party Wins Election in Blow to the Far Right

author: Jennah Haque
description: New York voters are turning out early in high numbers for a mayoral race that’s captured the country’s attention.
title: NYC Early Voting Surges Ahead of Nov. 4 Mayoral Election

author: Kristina Peterson, Gregory Korte
description: About 42 million Americans could see their food assistance cut off within days as the US government shutdown stretches toward its second month, threatening to deepen economic pain and test Washington’s resolve in one of the longest funding lapses in US history.
title: Millions to Lose Food Aid With Shutdown Dragging Into November

author: Eliyahu Kamisher
description: California Governor Gavin Newsom is betting his political future on a controversial ballot measure that would redraw the state’s congressional maps to favor Democrats. A coalition of super wealthy and working people is giving him a big financial advantage.
title: Newsom Trounces Republicans With $120 Million Prop 50 Campaign Haul

author: Simon Marks
description: A long-simmering dispute between Sudan’s army and a paramilitary group exploded into a full-blown civil war in April 2023. The following year, the US estimated that at least 150,000 people may have been killed. The toll has risen markedly since then, and there’s no sign of a lull in the fighting.
title: Sudan Is Being Ravaged by a Civil War the World Has Overlooked

author: Sarah Jacob, Elisabeth Behrmann, William Wilkes
description: Nexperia halted supplies to its China factory over disagreements with the site’s management, potentially escalating the standoff that’s already impacting automotive production in Europe and beyond.
title: Nexperia Halts China Shipments as VW Supplier Slows Output

author: Alberto Nardelli
description: The European Union is weighing a new trade measure that would require some Chinese exporters to supply critical raw materials to the bloc’s stockpiles when shipping certain goods into the EU.
title: EU Debates ‘In-Kind’ China Tariff to Ensure Critical Materials

author: Zoe Tillman
description: Federal courts are scaling back operations after exhausting reserve funds during the US government shutdown. But dozens of fights over President Donald Trump’s controversial policies are moving forward after judges rebuffed the administration’s requests for delays.
title: Judges Keep Trump Policy Fights Moving as Shutdown Hits Courts

author: Anthony Halpin
description: If Putin’s nuclear move was intended to pressure Trump into reviving a summit, it’s had little effect.
title: Trump Calls Putin’s Bluff on Nuke Showmanship

author: Kati Pohjanpalo
description: Finland plans to exclude high-risk vendors from a bigger portion of its fifth-generation mobile network in line with a push by the European Union to boost telecommunications security across the bloc.
title: Finland to Tighten Huawei Ban in 5G Network on Security Grounds

author: William Horobin
description: France’s Socialist Party leader Olivier Faure said he’s seeking a compromise with the government to make the budget work, easing back from brinkmanship that risks toppling Prime Minister Sebastien Lecornu.
title: France’s Socialists Seek Compromise as Budget Showdown Looms

author: Fabienne Kinzelmann, Bastian Benrath-Wright
description: Switzerland’s top trade diplomat made three trips to Washington since outsized US tariffs came into effect in August as Bern attempts to negotiate a lower rate.
title: Swiss Trade Diplomat Took Three US Trips as Tariff Talks Pick Up

author: Philip Heijmans
description: The Philippines’ top defense official called for deeper military ties with the US in a bid to face down mutual threats amid worsening relations with Beijing.
title: Philippines Calls For Deeper US Military Ties to Deter China

author: Zoltan Simon
description: Hungarian Prime Minister Viktor Orban said he saw little scope for accelerated economic growth before Russia’s war on Ukraine ends, climbing down from optimistic forecasts before elections next year.
title: Orban Says Economic Upswing Remains Distant Ahead of Elections

author: John Liu, Jing Li, Lucille Liu
description: After Donald Trump and Xi Jinping met in South Korea on Oct. 30, China released a statement on the outcomes of the landmark summit while US officials made public remarks.
title: Here’s How US, China Statements Compared After Xi-Trump Summit

author: Jim Wyss
description: Military jets are descending on the US territory that’s become a staging ground for Trump’s deadly strikes on drug boats.
title: Trump’s Use of Puerto Rico Navy Base for Drug War Stirs Tensions

author: Jason Leopold, Jeff Kao, Max Abelson, Harry Wilson, Ava Benny-Morrison, Surya Mattu
description: As investigators followed Jeffrey Epstein’s money in 2007, his elite team of attorneys waged an aggressive battle to stop them. A cache of private emails obtained by Bloomberg News reveals details of the fight.
title: Jeffrey Epstein Went to War Over Money Laundering Probe in 2007 Sex Case

author: Weilun Soon
description: A tanker carrying a cargo of Russian crude from recently-sanctioned Rosneft PJSC has been holding off Mumbai for a week amid intense scrutiny of Indian refiners’ purchases following the US curbs.
title: Oil Tanker With Cargo From Curb-Hit Rosneft Idles Off Mumbai

author: Donato Paolo Mancini, Chiara Albanese
description: Giorgia Meloni’s allies are exploring changes to Italy’s election laws that would boost her reelection odds, as internal polls show she may struggle to retain a majority in the upper house of parliament.
title: Meloni Weighs Overhaul of Italy’s Voting Laws to Help Reelection

author: Brian Platt
description: Canadian Prime Minister Mark Carney said his government will soon announce more than 20 investments in critical minerals projects, with a total value of about C$2 billion ($1.4 billion).
title: Canada to Unveil Billions in Mining Deals at G-7 Energy Summit

author: Erica Yokoyama, Keiko Ujikane
description: Japan should not rule out any funding options including debt issuance for its upcoming economic package, according to the minister tasked with compiling the measures.
title: Japan’s Kiuchi Doesn’t Rule Out Bonds to Fund Economic Package

author: James Mayger, Brian Platt, Josh Xiao
description: Canada’s Prime Minister Mark Carney hailed a “turning point” in his nation’s ties with China after a meeting with Chinese Xi Jinping that marked the first formal sitdown in eight years between leaders of the two nations.
title: China, Canada Leaders Meet For the First Time Since 2017 to Reset Ties

author: Helen Nyambura
description: Tanzania’s military said it’s been working with other security forces to quell unrest after protesters took to the streets over this week’s election that barred key opposition figures.
title: Tanzania Army Chief Calls for Calm as Election Unrest Escalates

author: Irina Anghel
description: UK home prices rose for a second straight month, in signs that prospective buyers remain resilient in the face of growing speculation of tax rises at the government’s November budget, according to a new report.
title: UK House Prices Increase Again in October, Nationwide Says

author: Sakura Murakami
description: China’s President Xi Jinping and Japan’s new Prime Minister Sanae Takaichi had their first formal meeting on the sidelines of the APEC conference Friday, as tensions spanning from trade to security continue to simmer between the two countries.
title: Chinese and Japanese Leaders Meet to Talk Rare Earths, Security

author: Aaron Eglitis
description: Latvia’s parliament voted to exit an international convention that combats violence against women, in a push by right-wing parties which claim the treaty promotes LGBTQ rights in the Baltic nation.
title: Latvian Lawmakers Vote to Leave Treaty on Violence Against Women

author: Nicholas Comfort
description: Two of Europe’s top banking watchdogs want to speed up work that could give lenders quicker approvals for plans to buy back shares or call bonds.
title: EU Banks Could Get Quicker Buyback Approvals, Top Watchdog Says

author: Sudhi Ranjan Sen, Philip Heijmans
description: US Defense Secretary Pete Hegseth said military ties with India have “never been stronger” following a meeting with his counterpart Rajnath Singh, signaling that trade tensions have not affected broader strategic cooperation.
title: US Says India Defense Ties ‘Never Been Stronger’ Amid Trade Rift

author: Patrick Van Oosterom, Charlotte Hughes-Morgan, Sarah Jacob
description: In more than one way, Rob Jetten, the head of the liberal D66 party who might become the next Dutch prime minister, offers a stark contrast to Geert Wilders, the divisive anti-migrant lawmaker who heads the far-right Freedom Party.
title: Dutch Set for Youngest Premier After Pro-EU Leader Wins Election

author: Netty Idayu Ismail
description: Malaysian Prime Minister Anwar Ibrahim’s trade deal with the US is drawing fire at home as a group of lawmakers question clauses that allow Washington to raise new tariffs and pressure the Southeast Asian nation to align with its trade policies.
title: Malaysia Trade Deal Fuels Concerns of Sovereignty, New US Levies

author: Sanne Wass
description: With NATO’s Arctic footprint expanding, Denmark is raising its military commitment to a territory seen as crucial to security — and focusing east.
title: For Danish Army, the Threat to Greenland Isn’t Trump But Russia

author: Jenny Leonard, Shawn Donnan, Joe Deaux
description: Donald Trump sounded triumphant afterwards. But in his first meeting with Chinese counterpart Xi Jinping since returning to office in January, the US president had to give at least as much as he got.
title: Trump Touts Rare-Earth Win in Talks That Showed Xi’s Strong Hand

author: Hallie Gu, Alfred Cang
description: China bought at least four more US soybean cargoes following a summit between President Donald Trump and his counterpart Xi Jinping, offering some relief to American farmers frozen out of the trade.
title: China Buys Four More US Soybean Cargoes Following Trade Deal

author: Skylar Woodhouse
description: President Donald Trump called on Senate Republicans to vote to get rid of the filibuster in the upper chamber, amid a government shutdown that has lasted nearly a month.
title: Trump Says GOP Should Ditch Filibuster Over Shutdown Stalemate

author: Iain Marlow, Philip Heijmans
description: Defense Secretary Pete Hegseth voiced serious concerns in talks with Chinese Defense Minister Dong Jun about Beijing’s naval activity around Taiwan and the South China Sea, citing its impact on US security partners in the Indo-Pacific.
title: Hegseth and China’s Defense Minister Meet After Trump-Xi Trade Truce

author: Josh Xiao
description: Chinese leader Xi Jinping warned against “breaking supply chains,” in his first public remarks after a landmark meeting with US President Donald Trump that secured a one-year truce in the world’s biggest trade fight.
title: Xi Calls for Stable Supply Chains After Sealing Trump Truce

author: Erica Yokoyama
description: The Japanese government is monitoring the yen with a strong sense of urgency, Finance Minister Satsuki Katayama said, sending her first clear warning on currency movements since taking on her role.
title: Japan’s Katayama Warns on FX as Yen Hits 8-Month Low After BOJ

author: Philip Heijmans
description: The US and Malaysia signed a pact solidifying bilateral defense ties, underscoring a commitment to security in the disputed South China Sea.
title: US and Malaysia Boost Security Partnership in South China Sea

author: Brendan Murray
description: Tucked into President Donald Trump’s trade deals formalizing higher tariffs on goods from Asia this week are provisions for a global economic frontier the US wants to stay free of protectionism: digital commerce.
title: Trump Pushes for a US-Led Digital Economy That’s Free of Tariffs
